[2
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 1998 15:10:07 +0800 (CST)
From: Chwan-Chuen King <a1234567@ccms.ntu.edu.tw>

The important thing to learn from Taiwan and Malaysia EV-71 epidemics is to
teach parents directly not only on watching the early symptoms/signs but
also the prevention precautions. The leadership including clinicians,
pathologists, virologists, epidemiologists, and neurologists is quite
important. Prevention of infection is always more efficient than curing
cases.
Once parents are taught properly, the chain of transmission will be more
effectively interrupted. However, we still have to pay more attention
until the true ending of this epidemic. Several autopsy cases did not show
myocarditis. Therefore, the pathogenesis of EV71 is worthwhile pursuing,
its mechanism in the damage
in brain stem and later pathogenesis in secondary organs.
--
Chwan-Chuen King, Dr.P.H.
Epidemiol. of Infectious Disease Lab.
College of Public Health
National Taiwan University
Taipei, Taiwan (100), R.O.C.
e-mail: a1234567@ccms.ntu.edu.tw
